commit.message:
Fix defcustom warnings

* mime-view.el (mime-display-text/plain-flowed-fill-column): Fix
misplaced :tag.

* mime-edit.el (mime-edit-message-max-lines-alist): Update :ty@pe
declaration.
(mime-edit-pgp-filtered-validities): Fix misplaced :tag.

Add major-mode clue to entity situations

It is for customizability depending on major-mode of preview
buffer.

* mime-view.el: Likewise.

* mime-image.el: Likewise.

* semi-setup.el: Likewise.

Minor refining previous commit

* mime-shr.el (mime-shr-allowed-images): Describe availability.
(shr-allowed-images): Remove definition.
(mime-shr-preview-text/html): Adjust indent (cosmetic change).
Merge branch 'LdBeth-semi-1_14-wl' into semi-1_14-wl

Support shr-allowed-images variable

Emacs 29 supports shr-allowed-images as a whitelist
variable for images allowed to be displayed. This
variable has lower piority than the blacklist
variable shr-blocked-images.

Update mime-shr.el to support set both the old blacklist
and whitelist. If shr-allowed-images does not exists,
only, mime-shr-blocked-images would taken effect.

* mime-shr.el (mime-shr-allowed-images): New variable.
(mime-shr-blocked-images): Update docstring.
(mime-shr-preview-text/html): Set shr-allowed-images.
* mime-pgp.el: Suppress byte-compiler's warning.

Update document for tag syntax

* mime-edit.el: Update tag syntax in comments.

* mime-ui-en.texi (mime-edit-mode): Update description of tag
syntax.

* mime-ui-ja.texi (mime-edit-mode): Likewise.
* mime-view.el (mime-view-nobreak-char-display): Fix typo.

Update docstring syntax

"'" in docstring has become special character since emacs 25.
Non-special "'" should be escaped.  And, some '(' characters are
escaped with single "\" to avoid mis syntax highlighting.  But the
problem looks to be fixed already.  So I remove the workaround.

* mime-edit.el (mime-prompt-for-parameter): Likewise.

* semi-def.el (mime-add-condition): Likewise.

mime-vcard.el requires bbdb-vcard-vcard21 in bbdb-vcard package

mime-vcard.el required vcard.el which was imcompatible with ELPA's
vcard package.  the ancient vcard.el is now renamed to
bbdb-vcard-vcard21.el and in MELPA's bbdb-vcard package.

* SEMI-ELS: Check bbdb-vcard-vcard21.el for mime-vcard.el.

* mime-vcard.el: Require bbdb-vcard-vcard21.el.

Remove XEmacs related stuff

* Makefile (package, install-package): Removed.

* SEMI-ELS: Likewise.

* SEMI-MK (config-semi-package, compile-semi-package)
(install-semi-package): Removed.

New installer option PACKAGE_LISPDIR

Specified directory and subdirectories are added to load-path
while compile and installation process.  Typically used for making
elisp files installed via package system visible from installer.
When variable name is specified, use its value as the root
directory.  Default value is 'package-user-dir'.  To disable the
feature, set value to 'NONE'.

* Makefile (PACKAGE_LISPDIR): New variable.
(elc, install-elc): Call emacs with PACKAGE_LISPDIR.

* SEMI-CFG: Add directory and subdirectories of PAKCAGE_LISPDIR to
load-path.

* SEMI-MK (config-semi): Set PAKCAGE_LISPDIR from arguments.

Fold docstring within 80 characters

* mime-edit.el (mime-edit-insert-file-as-text)
(mime-edit-pgp-keys-valid-key, mime-edit-sign-pgp-nonmime)
(mime-edit-encrypt-pgp-nonmime): Likewise.

* mime-view.el (mime-display-multipart/multilingual): LIkewise.

Check mule-version's availability

The variable is marked as obsolete in trunk.

* mime-edit.el (mime-edit-user-agent-value): Likewise.
* semi-setup.el: Adjust dependencies.

Fold docstring of customizable variable within 80 characters

* mime-shr.el (mime-shr-blocked-images): Likewise.

* mime-signature.el (mime-edit-signature-separator)
(mime-edit-default-signature, mime-edit-signature-alist): Likewise.

* mime-view.el (mime-view-text/html-previewer-alist)
(mime-view-text/html-previewer)
(mime-view-type-subtype-score-alist): Likewise.

Use threads for signature verification

When mime-pgp-use-concurrency is non-nil and Emacs supports
concurrency feature (Emacs 26 and later), signature verifation is
done in its own thread.

* mime-pgp.el (mime-pgp-concurrency-available-p): New function.
(mime-pgp-use-concurrency): New customizable variable.
(mime-pgp-make-mutex, mime-pgp-with-mutex): New functions.
(mime-pgp-mutex): New variable.
(mime-pgp-decrypt-string, mime-pgp-verify-string)
(mime-verify-application/*-signature-internal): Call EasyPG
functions with mutex if available.
(mime-preview-application/*-signature): Call EasyPG function with
mutex and thread if available.
* mime-pgp.el (mime-preview-application/pgp-encrypted): Fix typo.

Fix ignored argument for mime-display-text/plain-flowed

* mime-view.el (mime-display-text/plain-flowed): Fix the bug that
argument BUFFER is always ignored.
* mime-play.el: Suppress error in native compilation.

Fix error when attaching binary file without inputting parameters.

* mime-edit.el (mime-edit-insert-binary-file): Fallback encoding
to "base64" when unspecified.

Remove redundant check in mime-display-text/plain-flowed

* mime-view.el (mime-display-text/plain-flowed): Remove redundant
check for the last character.  it has been done by caller.
* mime-tnef.el: Use lexical binding.

Suppress byte-compiler's warnings.

* mime-edit.el: Require epa.el always.  Remove autoload cookie and
non-toplevel require function to load epa.el.

* mime-pgp.el (mime-preview-application/pgp-encrypted)
(mime-preview-application/pkcs7-mime): Require mmbuffer.el when
needed.

* mime-tnef.el: Require mmgeneric.el at compile time.
(mime-display-application/ms-tnef): Require mmbuffer.el when
needed.

* mime-play.el (mime-view-temp-message-buffer):
* mime-view.el (mime-preview-condition):
Move defition in front of the first reference.

* mime-w3.el (mime-put-keymap-region): Define at compile time too.
(mime-preview-text/html): remove use of
mime-save-background-color.  It does nothing.
(url-cid, mime-preview-text/html): Suppress byte-compiler's
warning.

* semi-setup.el (mime-view-text/html-previewer-alist)
(mime-view-text/html-previewer):Define as dynamic binding when
needed.

mime-view-nobreak-char-display variable is introduced.

* mime-view.el (mime-view-nobreak-char-display): New variable.
(mime-display-message): Make `nobreak-char-display'
buffer local and override it by mime-view-nobreak-char-display's
value.

Fix the last change

* mime-edit.el (mime-edit-user-agent-value): Remove string for
unibyte mode.

Update package description file for MELPA.

* semi-pkg.el: Define supported Emacs version.  Explicitly define
dependency on apel, because SEMI-EPG actually have direct
dependency on APEL-LB.

Code clean up.

* mime-view.el (mime-display-multipart/multilingual-prefered-languages)
(mime-view-read-situation-examples-file)
(mime-save-situation-examples):
* mime-edit.el (mime-edit-user-agent-value)
(mime-edit-insert-text):
* semi-def.el:
Remove code for old platforms.

* mime-edit.el (mime-edit-insert-file-filename)
(mime-edit-normalize-body): Assume FLIM-LB.
Merge branch 'conao3-remove-cvs' into semi-1_14-wl

remove cvs related contents

* Makefile (tar): Removed.
